Eurasian Natural Resources Corp.
Chairman Johannes Sittard plans to step down from the board
following a corporate governance review, which is scheduled to
report at the end of the summer, the  Daily Telegraph  reported,
without attribution. Sittard told ENRC directors last month that
he is willing to resign once a new boardroom structure has been
established, the Telegraph said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
